@node eplay "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Xaround" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, the game requires a 68020(+)
Amiga with Workbench 2.0 or higher and a Workbench with at least
8 colours.

                             How to play?

  The game consists of an area represented by a structure of a
variable size and shape that contains small blocks linked between
them. Square zones, each surrounded by 4 small blocs linked
together, are placed here and there on the game board. An 'X' shape
is shown on a 'pressed down' block, which constitutes the starting
block.

  To play, just click on a block that is linked and next to the
block occupied by the coloured 'X' shape (you can also use the
cursor keys to move the X shape). When you have moved around a
square zone that is connected by 4 links, that zone will then be
colourized.

  When all square zones have been colourized, return to the
starting block (the one that is pressed down), to complete the game
board...

  You can restart a game board by clicking on the 'Replay' button.

  To change the colour of the X shape, just click on it, or press
the space bar.

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

@endnode

